title: Nick Jonas seems tense in his new music video for 'Area Code'
text:
Friday, Oct 9 2015, 20:00   Google+ Nick Jonas has released his new music video for 'Area Code' - and it's pretty tense.Shot in black and white with mixed exposures and negatives, it's a far cry from his Jonas Brothers material - and that's before taking into account a decent amount of adult language .Jonas is depicted in different states of distress and anxiety, making it slightly uncomfortable viewing.He is also shown preparing to go on stage to perform to a gig of adoring fans. 
Â© YouTube / NickJonasVEVO Jonas's new album will drop early 2016 , with the singer saying it will feature tracks "with some more soul and R&B sounds, even hip-hop influences".The release will be the follow-up to 2014's Nick Jonas , which included UK number 2 single 'Jealous'.
